/*
 * DEPRECATED — the hand-written kl,dma-ether overlay used to live here. It carried
 * Zynq addresses (csr 0x43c00000, dma 0x40410000) and could not describe the
 * fully-FPGA NaxRiscv/LiteX build, where the same hardware lives at csr 0x90000000
 * and the DMA engines are LiteX CSRs at 0xf0002800.
 *
 * The overlay is now GENERATED per-platform from a small intermediate JSON (IR) so it
 * converges for any SoC. Use the generated files instead:
 *
 *     milan-nic.litex.dtsi   fully-FPGA NaxRiscv/LiteX build   (from ir/milan-dt.litex.json)
 *     milan-nic.zynq.dtsi    Zynq-7000 build                   (from ir/milan-dt.zynq.json)
 *
 * Regenerate:  ./milan_dt.py gen ir/milan-dt.<platform>.json > milan-nic.<platform>.dtsi
 * See README.md for the full flow and how to add a new platform.
 */
